'''[[Jay Ruby]]''' (1935- ) is an American scholar who was a professor in the [http://www.temple.edu/anthro/viscom.htm Department of Anthropology] at [[Temple University]] until his recent retirement.  He received his B.A. in History (1960) and Ph.D. in Anthropology (1969) from the [[University of California, Los Angeles]]. 

He is a leader in the field of [[visual anthropology]].

==Filmography==
* ''Rebekah and Sophie: A Lesbian Family'' (2005)
* ''Taylor Family Portrait'' (2005)
* ''Dear Old Oak Parkers'' (2006)
* ''Oak Park Regional Housing Center'' (2006)
* ''Val'' (2006)

